            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (q,S,q'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0181.xml" title="Region of an NFA" addr="jms-0181" type="local">region</fr:link> in an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017H.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017H" type="local">NFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>. The <html:em><html:strong><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">formal language</fr:link> accepted within <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (q,S,q'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex></html:strong></html:em> is defined to be the following set of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">strings</fr:link>:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \mathcal {L}_{M}{\mathopen {}\left (q,S,q'\right )\mathclose {}} =
 {\mathopen {}\left \{u \in \Sigma _M^\star \,\middle \vert \,
   q \mathrel {\vphantom {\xrightarrow {u}}\smash {\xrightarrow {u}}^*}
 q'
   \text { with all intermediate states lying in S}
 \right \}\mathclose {}}
]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>We shall also refer to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}_{M}{\mathopen {}\left (q,S,q'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the <html:em><html:strong>regional language</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (q,S,q'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
